      "side": 1,
      "message": "[Critical] Line 129: Expired pushes return before arming a deactivation check. If the app is cold-started in the background and accounts are active, an expiration-only push will not create or conclude a background episode, so the accounts may remain active until another lifecycle/push event. The comment says the caller re-arms the check, but this method is the serialized scheduling entry point. Schedule a background deactivation for expiration-only pushes without extending grace/restoring accounts.",
