      "side": 1,
      "message": "[Critical] Line 163: The episode cap also overrides CALL_PUSH_GRACE_MS. If a call push arrives after MAX_BACKGROUND_ACTIVE_MS has elapsed and the call has not yet reached an active/pending state, the next deactivation run can immediately deactivate accounts during the call negotiation path. That contradicts the stated goal of protecting call pushes. Track whether the current grace window is call-related and exempt that window from the cap, or reset/conclude the episode before restoring for a call push so it receives the full call grace period.",
      "revId": "9f5b24ed439d3340bcb9964cce4182c6f8b565b0",
